  "local_port": 45074,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I find a power outlet for my laptop at Melbourne Airport?",
  "response": "Finding a power outlet for your laptop at Melbourne Airport (officially known as Tullamarine Airport, MEL) should be relatively straightforward, as the airport is well-equipped to accommodate travelers' needs. Here are some tips and specific locations where you can charge your devices:\n\n### **1. Terminals and Seating Areas**\n- **Terminal 2 and Terminal 1**: Both terminals offer numerous seating areas with accessible power outlets. Look for charging stations near gates, seating lounges, and in designated charging zones.\n- **Arrivals and Departures Areas**: Throughout the main areas of both terminals, especially near cafes and restaurants, you\u2019ll often find power outlets available for public use.\n\n### **2. Lounges**\n- **Airline Lounges**: If you have access to an airline lounge (through business class tickets, lounge memberships, or day passes), these lounges typically provide ample charging facilities, including USB ports and standard power sockets.\n  - **Qantas Club**\n  - **Virgin Australia Lounge**\n  - **SkyTeam Lounge**\n- **Pay-Per-Use Lounges**: Lounges like the Plaza Premium Lounge offer access for a fee and provide charging facilities.\n\n### **3. Charging Stations and USB Outlets**\n- **Charging Points**: Look for dedicated charging stations equipped with multiple outlets and USB ports. These are usually located in waiting areas and near gate areas.\n- **Plug Points**: Standard power outlets (Type I) are available throughout the terminals for plugging in laptops and other devices.\n\n### **4. Shops and Cafes**\n- **Retail Stores and Coffee Shops**: Many of the airport\u2019s cafes, such as Starbucks and Caff\u00e8 Nero, offer power outlets for customers. Even if you're just stopping by for a quick drink or snack, you can take the opportunity to charge your laptop.\n- **Newsstands and Bookstores**: Some retail areas provide charging facilities or have products like power banks available for purchase.\n\n### **5. Airport Facilities and Information Desks**\n- **Information Kiosks**: If you're having trouble locating a power outlet, the airport\u2019s information desks can guide you to the nearest available charging point.\n- **Free Wi-Fi Zones**: Areas designated for free Wi-Fi often have charging facilities as well.\n\n### **6. USB Ports and Wireless Charging**\n- **USB Charging Ports**: In addition to standard power outlets, many areas offer USB ports for charging devices without the need for adapters.\n- **Wireless Charging Stations**: Some modern charging stations may include wireless (Qi) charging pads for compatible devices.\n\n### **Tips for Charging at Melbourne Airport**\n- **Bring Your Own Chargers and Adapters**: While the airport provides standard Type I power sockets, having your own chargers with multiple plugs or a universal adapter can be convenient.\n- **Portable Power Banks**: Consider carrying a fully charged power bank as a backup in case you cannot find an available outlet.\n- **Check Airport Maps**: Visit the [Melbourne Airport Official Website](https://www.melbourneairport.com.au/) for detailed terminal maps and updates on available facilities.\n\n### **Contact Information**\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, you can contact Melbourne Airport directly:\n- **Website**: [www.melbourneairport.com.au](https://www.melbourneairport.com.au/)\n- **Customer Service**: Check the website for specific contact details and support options.\n\nBy exploring these options, you should be able to find a convenient place to charge your laptop and stay connected during your time at Melbourne Airport.\n\nSafe travels!",
